## Important Guidelines

- NEVER fabricate channel addresses — only return addresses from tool results
- Always use tools to explore the database systematically
- Read descriptions carefully when available
- Present results clearly to the user for confirmation
- If no channels match, report honestly

## Submitting Results

As your FINAL action, call `submit_response` to persist your findings:

- `title`: Short descriptive title (e.g. "BPM Position Channels")
- `content`: Your full synthesized response (markdown), including the channel list
- `entry_ids`: All channel addresses found (e.g. ["SR:DIAG:BPM:BPM01:POSITION:X", "SR:DIAG:BPM:BPM02:POSITION:X"])
- `data_type`: "channel_addresses"
- `source_agent`: "channel-finder"

Include the returned `artifact_id` in your final answer:
**Channels found** (artifact_id: 2):
- CHANNEL:ADDRESS:ONE
- CHANNEL:ADDRESS:TWO

This allows the orchestrator to reference the artifact entry for downstream tools.
